criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. have been a patient at one of the participating FQHCs with at least one prior visit in
             the past 12 months;

          2. age 50 to 75 (based on USPSTF guidelines);

          3. English-speaking.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. have a previous history of cancer other than non-melanoma skin cancer;

          2. are up-to-date with CRC screening according to USPSTF guidelines (FOBT in less than a
             year, sigmoidoscopy less than 5 years, or colonoscopy less than 10 years);

          3. a family history that requires a more complete history and possible colonoscopy
             because of their risk factor;

          4. have a documented or uncorrectable cognitive, hearing, or visual impairment;

          5. are too ill to participate
